            . I am a watch and clock maker, and live in Duke-street, Aldgate. The timepiece is worth no more than 30 s.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I called at the door, and knocked once or twice but got no answer, the timepiece lay on the shop board, and something on the floor; I was coming into the shop, as I wanted some steaks; she came and said I was robbing the place.</p>
               <p>MRS. HEMPSON. He had it under his jacket.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 40.</p>
